  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT41-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṭai vēṟupāṭu kaṇṭu kavaṉṟa tōḻikkuk kiḻatti uraittatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Declared by HER to the confidante who was anxious on seeing changes [in her] during the time of separation.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT41">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                kātala ruḻaiya rākap perituvantu</l>
<l>                cāṟuko ḷūriṟ pukalvēṉ maṉṟa</l>
<l>                vatta naṇṇiya vaṅkuṭic cīṟūr</l>
<l>                makkaḷ pōkiya vaṇilāṭu muṉṟiṟ</l>
<l>                pulappil pōlap pulleṉ</l>
<l>                ṟalappeṉ ṟōḻiyava rakaṉṟa ñāṉṟē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
               <l rend="indent">When<note place="foot">In this version the infinitive <term xml:lang="ta">āka</term> is to be understood as a conditional which is not impossible, for sure, but also not very usual.</note> [my] lover is close, greatly delighted<note place="foot">Instead of <term xml:lang="ta">peritu uvantu</term> it is also possible to read <term xml:lang="ta">peritu vantu</term>: "as something big has come", that is: like a village having a festival for a special occasion.</note>,</l>
               <l rend="indent2">like a village taking a festival,</l>
               <l rend="indent4">I rejoice, certainly.</l>
               <l rend="indent">Near the road, in a small village with pretty homes<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">am kuṭi</term>: rendered by TVG as "with good inhabitants", that is, <term xml:lang="ta">kuṭi</term> is meant to denote the inhabitants of the <term xml:lang="ta">ūr</term>. Cf., though, the descending climax of KT 130.3f. <term xml:lang="ta">nāṭu</term> – <term xml:lang="ta">ūr</term> – <term xml:lang="ta">kuṭi</term> where <term xml:lang="ta">kuṭi</term> is obviously the smallest habitation unit.</note></l>
               <l rend="indent2">people gone, squirrels playing in the front-yard,</l>
               <l rend="indent">a house left lonely – like that, empty,</l>
               <l>I am in distress, friend, since he left.</l>
               <lg type="alternate" resp="#Srin">
                <l>Because [my] lover is a tough worker (cf. DED 586; āka as bhavati),</l>
                <l>I will rejoice like the people of an ūr who are having a festival, for sure (i.e. when he comes back</l>
                <l>as a wealthy man who is able to marry me), (but for the time being,) while he is away I will be</l>
                <l>afflicted ...</l>
               </lg>
                    </lg>
                

                
                
        </div>
